<HEAD>New AP Correspondent Named for San Diego</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   David Sedeno, Associated Press correspondent in
San Antonio, Texas, for three years, has been named correspondent in
charge of the AP's San Diego bureau.
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Los Angeles Chief of
Bureau Andy Lippman.
   Sedeno, 27, joined the AP in Dallas in 1984 and became Harlingen
correspondent the following year.
   He is a native of San Angelo, Texas, and a graduate of Angelo
State University. Sedeno was a copy editor for the San Angelo
Standard-Times before joining the AP.
