<FIRST>r i PM-Lebanon     06-22 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lebanon,0198</SECOND>
<HEAD>Grenade Explodes Near British Consulate In Lebanon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One man was killed and another wounded
when a hand grenade exploded in their car near the British Consulate
in east Beirut, police said today.
   There was no immediate explanation for the explosion, which
occurred late Wednesday in the Jal el-Dib district. The wounded man
was taken to a hospital, ``and he'll be interrogated later,'' said a
police spokesman, who cannot be identified under standing
regulations.
   He also said Syrian and Christian gunners traded howitzer and
machine gun fire in and around Beirut overnight and that seven
people were wounded.
   The latest casualties raised the toll to 373 people killed and
1,457 wounded since March 8, when the latest round of fighting began
in Lebanon's 14-year-old civil war.
   Also today, two Israeli warplanes flew an apparent reconnaissance
mission over Lebanon, one day after Israeli jet fighters blasted a
Palestinian guerrilla base south of Beirut. Police said one
guerrilla was killed and seven wounded in the air attack, the ninth
by Israel in Lebanon this year.
   The guerrillas belonged to Ahmed Jibril's Popular Front for the
Liberation of Palestine-General Command.
</TEXT>
