<HEAD>Pope Dedicates Peace Day to Ecology</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II has dedicated the church's
next World Day of Peace to the ecological crisis, the Vatican said
Thursday.
   Stressing that the goods of the Earth must not be used ``for
selfish ends, for profit or power alone,'' the Vatican said the need
to respect the environment is a new challenge to peace.
   ``Peace with God the Creator _ Peace with all of Creation'' is
the theme for the day, which the Roman Catholic Church marks on Jan.
1.
   The theme chosen by the pope, it said, is an invitation to
reflect on the ecological crisis from a moral perspective.
   ``The Earth and all that it contains are a common heritage for
humanity. This should be the governing principle for the use of the
goods of the Earth by nations and the international community to
which these goods are entrusted,'' the Vatican said.
</TEXT>
