<DOCNO> AP890622-0242 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-22-89 2220EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-DeathSquads     06-22 0265</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Death Squads,0272</SECOND>
<HEAD>Congressman Says Death Squads Target Colombia's Governing Party</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TOM WELLS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A congressman said Thursday that death
squads, possibly hired by drug traffickers, are hunting down members
of the governing Liberal Party.
   Rep. Jorge Infante Leal said in a communique sent to Liberal
leaders that more than 100 members were killed in the eastern plains
in the last year.
   The Defense Ministry confirmed his statements. The ministry said
previously that guerrillas of the Colombian Revolutionary Armed
Forces are targeting Liberal Party members.
   The guerrillas may be taking revenge for right-wing death squads
killing more than 800 members of Colombia's biggest leftist party,
the Patriotic Union, in four years.
   But El Tiempo newspaper quoted the congressman as saying he is
not entirely convinced that guerrillas are behind the killings of
Liberal Party members.
   Infante Leal said the gunmen could be hired by drug traffickers
who are killing Liberals because a Liberal faction has sought an
alliance with the Patriotic Union.
   Drug runners have been at war with guerrillas here for years
because of rebel attempts to kidnap drug traffickers or members of
their families and hold them for ransom.
   Also, drug traffickers resent guerrilla demands of payment of a
so-called revolution tax in areas where traffickers raise coca
plants for producing cocaine or where the traffickers have ranches,
national police have said.
   The Liberal Party members have been killed in Guaviare, Meta and
Vichada states, areas where coca bushes are grown in abundance and
where the Colombian Revolutionary Armed Forces have an estimated
5,000 guerrillas.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
