<DOCNO> AP890622-0243 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-22-89 2227EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--CrackRobbery     06-22 0171</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Crack Robbery,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police: Woman Steals $5 From Boy To Pay For Crack Habit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DELRAY BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman desperate for money to buy
crack cocaine stole $5 from a 7-year-old boy who was on his way to
the supermarket to pick up sausage and a loaf of bread, police said.
   Barbara Jean Malone, 29, of Delray Beach was being held Thursday
on $3,000 bond at the Palm Beach County Women's Stockade.
   Malone was caught by police Tuesday a few moments after she
allegedly shoved Christopher Moore against a wall and robbed him of
the $5 his mother gave him to buy food.
   ``That never happened to me before,'' Christopher, a first-grader
at Banyan Creek Elementary School, said Wednesday. ``I was crying. I
don't want to go up there anymore.''
   The sobbing boy ran to a police car at a nearby gas station, then
he and the officers drove around the neighborhood looking for the
robber. Police said Malone's actions were caused by her addiction to
crack cocaine.
</TEXT>
