<HEAD>Toronto Firm Buys Florida Weekly Shoppers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Toronto Sun Publishing Corp. has acquired
seven Central Florida weekly shopping guides and newspapers, along
with their printing plant, from Westminster Florida Inc. for $14.5
million.
   Included in the deal were the News-Gazette in Kissimmee and
shopping guides in Orlando, Kissimmee, Bradenton, Longboat Key,
Sarasota and Venice, along with the Bradenton plant that prints all
of them.
   Sun publisher Douglas Creighton said Tuesday he didn't plan any
changes at the publications.
   Creighton said he was also interested in Westminster's other
Florida free weekly publications in Jacksonville, Fort Pierce,
Sebring and Okeechobee. But he said he had not made a formal offer
for them.
   Sun Publishing sold the Houston Post to William D. Singleton in
1987.
