<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's economy continues to grow, but
there are ``ebbing rates of expansion'' in some regions, the Federal
Reserve said.
   The survey of economic conditions around the country indicated
that growth is slowing and inflationary pressures have eased in
response to an anti-inflation campaign launched by the Fed in March
1988.
   The report released Wednesday suggests the central bank need not
push up interest rates.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Paramount Communications Inc. stepped up its
pursuit of Time Inc. by asking the Delaware Chancery Court to block
Time's proposed $14 billion buyout of Warner Communications Inc.
   Paramount told the court Wednesday in a 49-page amendment to an
earlier suit that Time acted improperly in rejecting Paramount's
$10.7 billion offer and launching its own takeover bid for Warner.
