<TEXT>
   H. Robert Heller is resigning as one of the
seven members of the Federal Reserve Board, citing financial
hardships in living on his $82,500-a-year government salary.
   An expert in international economics, Heller said Wednesday he
would return to California to become an executive vice president of
Visa International, the giant credit card company.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Supreme Court gave railroads more freedom
to sell off rail lines without first negotiating with unions over
the effects of a sale, such as the loss of jobs.
   By a 5-4 vote on Wednesday, the court decided one of the most
critical issues facing the nation's railroad industry.
   It said the Pittsburgh &amp; Lake Erie Railroad, or P&amp;LE, may sell
its 182 miles of rail line in eastern Ohio and western Pennsylvania
without first negotiating with its employees' unions.
